1. Install git: sudo apt-get install git

2. Register on Github and verify email id provided
3. To configure settings::
git config --global user.name "Your Name Here"
git config --global user.email "your_email@youremail.com"
4. Create repository on Github â€“ testRepo or perform git init on terminal to initialize empty repo locally
5. mkdir ~/Repo1 will create Repo1 folder in home
6. go to Repo1 on terminal and then git clone https://github.com/dhanashrik/testRepo.git this will clone the repo and create folder structure inside Repo1

